end-time semantics; target event/exit/phase stay TRANSITIVELY enforced (verdict-gen's eligibility filter drops non-run/non-final/non-ok rows before the scorer, leaving any reference to them dangling and G0-invalid), a registered reliance, not an omission — verdict-gen passes eligible rows unchanged and the scorer is the resolution point), G1 extended with control-family acceptable sums == run-level acceptable total and strict integer typing of n_covered/n_control/dev_n/dev_parse_refused (dev_parse_refused <= dev_n), typed G2 gold counters, hardened G4 in-range division, AND the 14.10 item-B short-circuit (ASM-0625): any g1_counts failure returns a clean serializable INSTRUMENT-INVALID (gates populated, analysis block EMPTY, exit 0) BEFORE any Wilson/Holm/descriptive arithmetic, so no rejected denominator is ever computed over and malformed counts always reach the registered INSTRUMENT-INVALID verdict, never ERR_P2_ANALYSIS (the round-3 n_covered=True complex-Wilson and n_control=True TypeError paths are closed); G1 additionally types every remaining analysis-divided counter (label_strata, synonym-probe counters, frontend_total_ns when present) and non-dict metrics/pins_observed bodies fail closed instead of raising. Supersedes bcb9dfa6… (round-2-re-audit pin), 4a3c7551… (round-2 pin), 18c33ed3… (round-1 phrasing-pin) and 0e8e09b9… (freeze-candidate pin)."
